# Docs and Parity

## Before coding

1. Open matching PRD: `docs/modules/{module}/prds/`
2. Read flow overview: `docs/modules/{module}/flow/overview.md` (when present)
3. Read API module doc under `docs/api/modules/` — feature module names often differ from API file names:

   | Feature area | API doc |
   |--------------|---------|
   | sales | `outbound.md` (+ `invoicing.md` for invoices) |
   | purchase | `inbound.md` |
   | inventory | `inventory.md` |
   | ar | `ar.md` |
   | master-data | `master-data.md` |
   | auth / users | `auth.md`, `users.md` |
   | reports | `reports.md` |
   | system | `system.md`, `settings.md`, `audit.md` |

4. Check current status: `docs/parity/legacy-to-new-parity-matrix.md`
5. Do not contradict [brd-parity-and-changes.md §2](docs/brds/brd-parity-and-changes.md)

## Parity status legend

| Status | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| **Implemented** | Entity + API + frontend wired and usable |
| **Partial** | Some layers missing or not API-connected |
| **Missing** | Not built |
| **Dropped** | Intentionally excluded (document reason) |

## After coding

- Update the parity matrix row: status, backend, frontend, gap notes
- Link new PRDs from [docs/modules/README.md](docs/modules/README.md) if added
- Cross-check [docs/README.md](docs/README.md) deployment section when wiring status changes

## Don't

- Label **Implemented** when UI exists but is not API-connected
- Skip parity matrix updates “for later”
- Duplicate full PRD content in code comments — link the doc
